<p>I try to load a json file and and put the content in a <strong>listview with flipswitches at the right side.</strong></p>  <p>My HTML file with one example listview line, which is working fine (here without the first page and navbar to keep it clearly)</p>  <pre><code>&lt;head&gt; &lt;meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1"&gt; &lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="http://code.jquery.com/mobile/1.4.5/jquery.mobile-1.4.5.min.css"&gt; &lt;link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="liststyle.css"&gt; &lt;script src="http://code.jquery.com/jquery-1.11.3.min.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt; &lt;script src="http://code.jquery.com/mobile/1.4.5/jquery.mobile-1.4.5.min.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt; &lt;script type="text/javascript" src="script.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt; &lt;/head&gt; &lt;body&gt; &lt;div data-role="page" data-theme="b" id="pagetwo"&gt;   &lt;div data-role="main" class="ui-content" id="main"&gt;        &lt;ul data-role="listview" data-inset="true" id="alarmlist"&gt;       &lt;li data-role="fieldcontain"&gt;         &lt;a href="#pageone"&gt;Control&lt;/a&gt;         &lt;select id="test-slider" data-role="slider" name="testslider"&gt;           &lt;option value="off"&gt;off&lt;/option&gt;           &lt;option value="on"&gt;on&lt;/option&gt;         &lt;/select&gt;       &lt;/li&gt;     &lt;/ul&gt;   &lt;/div&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;/body&gt; </code></pre>  <p>and the linked liststyle.css</p>  <pre><code>.ui-li .ui-btn-inner a.ui-link-inherit, .ui-li-static.ui-li {     display: block !important;     padding: 0,9em 75px 0,9em 15px !important; } div.ui-slider-switch {     position: absolute;     right: 0;     width: 40%;     top: 12.5%; } </code></pre>  <p>and the code in the script.js file</p>  <pre><code>$("#pagetwo").on("pageshow" , function() {              var output = '';             for (var x in data.alarm) {                 output += '&lt;li data-role="fieldcontain"&gt;' +                     '&lt;a href="#"&gt;' + data["alarm"][x]["time"] +                  '&lt;select data-role="slider"&gt;' +                  '&lt;option value="off"&gt;off&lt;/option&gt;' +                 '&lt;option value="on"&gt;on&lt;/option&gt;&lt;/select&gt;' +                 '&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/li&gt;';              }             $('#alarmlist').append(output).listview("refresh"); }); </code></pre>  <p>Now i get this result: <a href="http://imageshack.com/a/img540/3844/dxuopI.png" rel="nofollow">http://imageshack.com/a/img540/3844/dxuopI.png</a></p>  <p>When i delete the <code>.on("pageshow" , function() {</code> and run both pages from start, i get a bit better result but also an error. <a href="http://imageshack.com/a/img538/9508/89jtvd.png" rel="nofollow">http://imageshack.com/a/img538/9508/89jtvd.png</a></p>